# Cursor Rules for CarbonPrint Project

## General Rules
- Follow the design rules in `design.rules`
- Use TypeScript for all new code
- Follow React best practices and hooks patterns
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling (v3.4.1)
- Maintain consistency with existing codebase patterns

## Context7 MCP Integration
- Automatically use Context7 MCP for code generation, library documentation, and setup instructions
- Use Context7 when user asks about frameworks, libraries, or APIs
- Prefer Context7 for getting up-to-date documentation and examples
- Use Context7 for version-specific library information

## Project-Specific Rules
- All colors must be HSL format (see `src/index.css`)
- Use shadcn-ui components from `src/components/ui/`
- Follow the existing component structure and naming conventions
- German language content for user-facing text
- Use Resend API for email functionality (see `RESEND_SETUP.md`)
- eBay button configuration in Navbar (see `EBAY_BUTTON_SETUP.md`)

## Code Quality
- Write clean, maintainable code
- Add proper TypeScript types
- Use meaningful variable and function names
- Follow the existing code style and formatting

